<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469900>
    dc:description "Figure 12. Prof.Dr.Rui Cerqueira at the VII Congresso Brasileiro de Mastozoologia, in Gramado, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, in 2014; in this congress, Rui received an award by the Sociedade Brasileira de Mastozoologia (SBMz) in recognition for his contribution to mammalogy; note that he is wearing the medal awarded to him by the American Society of Mammalogists in 2012 as honorary member. Photo by Ana Lazar." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469900/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469876>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Map of collecting localities of geographic samples of seven species of genus Euryoryzomys, based on the gazeưeer provided in Appendix I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469876/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469902>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Known collection localities of Euryoryzomys cerqueirai sp. nov, from Ceará and Paraíba. Green areas represent the Brejos de altitude, mountain forested areas within the Caatinga (in light ocher): A. Serra de Ibiapaba; B: Serra de Baturité; C. Brejo de Areia.Ceará:1. Sitio Corolero, Ibiapina; 2. São Benedito; 3. Guaraciaba do Norte; 4. Área do Ibama, Pacoti; 5. Sítio Friburgo, grota do Bananal, Pacoti; 6. Sítio Friburgo, grota do cafezal, Pacoti; 7. Sítio Friburgo, Sede do sítio, Pacoti; 8. Sede do Museu de História Natural do Ceará Prof. Dias da Rocha, Pacoti. 9. Sítio Sinimbu, Guaramiranga; Paraíba: 10. Areia.See Appendix I for detailed information on the collection localities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469902/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469892>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Dorsal and ventral views of the skins of two male specimens of Euryoryzomys sp. nov. from Serra de Baturité, Ceará, Brazil.From less to right, MZUSP 36044 (MRT 130); and MZUSP 36042 (MRT 46); external measurements are, respectively, HBL: 136 mm, TL: 167 mm; and HBL:136 mm, TL: 159 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469892/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469896>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Comparative plate of Euryoryzomys skulls, showing the variation of three selected qualitative traits, the presence of jugal (lateral view; A-E), depth of the zygomatic notch (dorsal view; F-H), and the shape of incisive foramina (ventral view; I-L). (A) E. russatus, MN81475; (B) Euryoryzomys sp. nov. CRB3688; (C) E. lamia, MN67090; (D) E.lamia, CRB1024; (E) Euryoryzomys sp. nov.MN37046. (F) E. russatus, MN81475; (G) E. lamia, MN67090; (H) Euryoryzomys sp. nov., MN37046. (I) Euryoryzomys sp. nov., CRB3688; (J) E.lamia, MN67090; (K) E. russatus, MN81475; (L) E. macconnelli, MN56817." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469896/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469898>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Dorsal, ventral and lateral views of the skull of specimen MZUSP 36044, male, the holotype of the new species of Euryoryzomys cerqueirai sp. nov., from Serra de Baturité, Ceará, Brazil.TOL = 35.11 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469898/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469904>
    dc:description "Figure 14. Ventral (less) and lateral (right) view of the phallus of Euryoryzomys cerqueirai sp. nov., MN42930, from Ibiapaba, Ceará, Brazil." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469904/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

